                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In like manner also, that women adorn themselves in modest apparel, with shamefacedness and sobriety; not with broided hair, or gold, or pearls, or costly array;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives; Woman.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastity; Modesty.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apparel.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0modesty, reverence.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0plaited, braided.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But (which becometh women professing godliness) with good works.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godliness.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the woman learn in silence with all subjection.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Silence.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But I suffer not a woman to teach, nor to usurp authority over the man, but to be in silence.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teaching.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0exercise dominion, be autocratic, domineer.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 57
                    },
